criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  They are ALYN patients undergoing physiotherapy for mild to severe ABI;

          -  They experience symptoms of vestibular function such as vertigo, postural instability,
             or impaired ocular motility;

          -  They are between the ages of 8 and 18;

          -  The time since injury/event is between 10 days and 1 year after the injury/event;

          -  They are able to maintain stable and dynamic positioning of the head;

          -  They able to walk with or without assistive equipment, or use a wheelchairs with no
             need for head support, defined by a LSS (level of sitting scale) score of 3 or greater
             (scale range: 1-8);

          -  Are able to understand basic instructions;

          -  Have sufficient visual acuity and visual field to identify and track mid-size objects
             on a screen.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Psychological, neurological or cognitive disorders which could impede participation,
             such as a history of epileptic seizures;

          -  Untreated benign paroxysmal positional vertigo (BPPV);

          -  Are in early post-operative stages (to avoid risk of bleeding or cerebrospinal fluid
             leak);

          -  Hearing impairment.
